Ekunola Davies Ministry International, otherwise known as Genesis Team International, holds its annual vigil Crusade 2022 under the aegis of Genesis Team International Crusade. The organisers said the programme, themed, ‘Abraham Obeyed My Voice’ and adopted from Genesis 26 verse 5, will hold at the Rehoboth Prayer Mountain, Araromi Oteyi Bus-Stop, Papa Ilaro Express Road, Ewekoro Local Government, Ogun State this weekend. Prophetic Evangelist Ekunola Davies, host of the crusade, said the reason for the 2022 GTI Crusade was to emphasise on the subject of obedience. 2022: Year Of Crown Of Glory But Pray Against Enemy’s… ‘Over 39.65m MSMEs Operate In Nigeria’ He stressed that Abraham, born before the time of Christ, was a friend of God and obeyed God, hence he was justified by his obedience and counted as a righteous man. Davies disclosed that Evang. Adebowale Adeboye, Prophet Isaac Badaru, Prophet Segun Babatunde, Prophet Samuel Bankole, Evang. Olayinka Ekunola, Evang. Samson Ojuolape, Prophet Arole Abass, Evang. Sam Awhasu would be ministering. Song ministration, he said, would be by Apostle Dan and GTI Marvellous Choir, among others.